 company to bid on a project to translate thousands of ordinary english words and phrases into arabic dari pashto urdu and uzbek the proposal offered scant details but the director of adex robert l addis thought he knew its purpose the words to be translated were conversational which seemed to rule out any technical legal financial or medical focus and pashto dari and uzbek are spoken in afghanistan and the other languages are common in the region technology briefing  software lernout sells a unit lionbridge technologies will buy the mendez unit of lernout  hauspie the troubled belgian speech technology company for  million in cash plus an additional  million to pay off mendez debt mendez a translation services and software provider had been for sale for months as part of lernout  hauspies bankruptcy restructuring the unit which is profitable has about  million in annual revenue and was initially valued at  million but the asking price was lowered repeatedly when few interested buyers appeared lionbridge based in waltham mass provides multilingual content management systems it said it would finance the purchase by selling preferred stock to institutional investors the transaction which is expected to be completed in the third quarter is subject to approval by courts in the united states and belgium jennifer  lee nyt company news lionbridge to buy intlcom for  million lionbridge technologies inc said yesterday that it had agreed to acquire intlcom a rival provider of software conversion and internet portal globalization services for about  million in stock lionbridge based in waltham mass and intl based in framingham mass both help multinational companies convert software translate help manuals and globalize web sites for use by people in their native languages lionbridge and intl will have a combined work force of  employees in  countries lionbridge had sales of  million in  shares of lionbridge rose  yesterday to  in nasdaq trading offering by lionbridge lionbridge